From Steve Moseley Subject Re Observation re helmets In article Ed Green Pixel Cruncher writes If your primary concern is protecting the passenger in the event of a crash have him or her fitted for a helmet that is their If your primary concern is complying with stupid helmet laws carry a real big spare you can put a big or small head in a big helmet but not in a small one So what should I carry if I want to comply with intelligent helmet laws The above comment in no way implies support for any helmet law nor should such support be A promise is a Steve Steve Moseley Microbiology SC Phone University of Washington FAX Seattle WA